cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.AR, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a security hardening technique and proposes a new implementation to improve its performance.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the design principle of separating mechanism and policy and proposes new algorithms to optimize the instrumentation policy for shadow stacks.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses binary static analysis and proposes new mechanism optimizations such as binary function inlining.
- cs.AR (Architecture) is relevant as the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed implementation using SPEC 2017 benchmarks.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a new implementation of a system-level security mechanism.
